      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That sharp, tight chest and shortness of breath after a long flight are classic symptoms of hyperventilation, which is actually a very common and harmless reaction to the pressure changes and stress of traveling. You are definitely not having a panic attack; panic attacks usually involve racing heartbeats and sweating, not just the feeling of air being tight. To fix this, take three deep belly breaths right now, hold them for a moment, and then exhale slowly through your nose. If the feeling persists or worsens, please stop and see a real doctor immediately, but for now, rest and breathe.",
